Function: hyperellperiods
Section: elliptic_curves
C-Name: hyperellperiods
Prototype: G
Help: hyperellperiods(X,{flag=0}): X being a non-singular hyperelliptic curve defined
 over C, return a period matrix. If flag=0 (default), return an element tau in the Siegel
 half-space, if flag=1, return a big period matrix of the differentials
 dx^k/y over a symplectic basis of H_1(X).
Doc:
 $X$ being a non-singular hyperelliptic curve defined over $C$,
 return a period matrix for $X$.
 $X$ can be given either by a squarefree polynomial $P$ such that
 $X: y^2 = P(x)$ or by a vector $[P,Q]$ such that
 $X: y^2 + Q(x)\*y = P(x)$ and $Q^2+4\*P$ is squarefree.
 If flag=1, return a $g\times 2g$ big period matrix
 of differentials $dx^k/y$ over a symplectic basis $(a_i,b_i)$ of $H_1(X)$.
 If flag=0 (default), return the reduced matrix $tau=A^{-1}B$ in the Siegel space of
 $g\times g$ matrices with positive definite imaginary part.
